Residents of Giyani in Limpopo continue to bear the brunt of corruption and a lack of service delivery. eNCA reporter Govan Whittles has more on this story. Courtesy of #DStv403 GIYANI - Thousands of residents in Giyani and surrounding Limpopo are still without basic needs, especially water. More than R3-billion has been spent on the Giyani Bulk Water Project so far, but the project is still incomplete. WATCH:Â Giyani Water Crisis | R3.5bn spent but still no water A water project that was meant to be completed in 2017 is gathering dust. Three officials have been arrested on corruption allegations.